                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="15119004" author="maximp" created="Wed, 27 Jan 2016 10:38:00 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;One more occurrence.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15119393" author="benedict" created="Wed, 27 Jan 2016 15:04:27 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Prior to &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-8099&quot; title=&quot;Refactor and modernize the storage engine&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CASSANDRA-8099&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;CASSANDRA-8099&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; the min/max buffers were &quot;minimized&quot; (i.e. they were extracted from whatever enclosing buffer they were sourced from, into their own heap allocation).  This is no longer the case, so the slabs they are allocated on get linked to, gradually consuming heap as more sstables are flushed (a restart will bring temporary respite).&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15121809" author="slebresne" created="Thu, 28 Jan 2016 16:16:43 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Yes, not minimizing the buffers is definitively an oversight. I&apos;ve push below a very simple patch to add it back, though for some reason I have a hard time getting a clean unit test run. Some tests seems to be timeouting or exiting anormaly but I see no reason for the patch the cause and I can&apos;t reproduce locally.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It might be a CI issue so I&apos;ll try re-running one more time but in the meantime, &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=benedict&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;benedict&quot;&gt;benedict&lt;/a&gt; do you time for a quick review of the patch on principle?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&apos;table-wrap&apos;&gt;
